      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It can certainly feel stressful, but think of the escrow agent not as a jailer, but as a highly disciplined, rule-following gatekeeper. Their power is strictly limited by the terms of the purchase agreement, which is the ultimate rulebook. They don't have personal opinions; they are just executing the contract, which is a much more predictable process than trying to negotiate with a nervous, greedy-looking third-party buyer or seller. It's a system designed to prevent the kind of chaos you'd get if everyone just started throwing their money around without oversight.",
